Cargese 99 NATO-ASI. Strict summary of a more extended version hep-th/9908189String theory on curved backgrounds has received much attention on account ofboth its own interest, and of its relation with gauge theories. Despite theprogress made in various directions, several quite elementary questions remainunanswered, in particular in the very simple case of three-dimensional anti-deSitter space. I briefly review these problems.